{
  "text": "Having a large population with rice as the staple crop, Asia has the biggest potential for bioethanol production. Asia could produce up to 291 Gl bioethanol per year. Rice, wheat straw and corn stover are the most favorable bioethanol feedstocks in Asia [CITATION_1] . Likewise, in Indonesia rice straw and corn stover will become a potential feedstock for lignocellulose ethanol production since the staple food of the population is rice and maize.",
